Notes: The St. Louis Rams signed G Rodger Saffold on March 14, 2014 to a five year contract worth $31,722,233. The contract contains $11 million in fully guaranteed salary. Saffold will receive a $5 million signing bonus and has a fully guaranteed base salary in 2014 and a protected $3 million roster bonus in 2015. If he is on the roster the 3rd day of the 2015 League Year his base salary will become fully guaranteed. His 2016 base salary can also become fully guaranteed if on the roster on the 3rd day of the 2016 season. From 2016 through 2018 Saffold can earn up tp $500,000 in gameday active roster bonuses. If he is on the Rams roster on the 3rd day of the 2018 League Year he will earn a $1 million roster bonus. Saffold can earn yearly playtime incentives of nearly $77,000 and escalators of $1.125 million. If Saffold is selected to a Pro Bowl or is named 1st team All NFL he has the right to void the final two seasons of the contract.
Name: Rodger Saffold

Notes: Cam Newton signed a five year, $103.8 million contract extension with the Panthers on June 2, 2015 containing $31 million fully guaranteed. Most of the information is based on numbers tweeted out by Joel Corry concerning the cap numbers of the contract. Newton received a $22.5 million signing bonus and $7.5 million roster bonus upon signing the contract. In 2016 he will receive a $10 million option bonus and his 2016 salary will become fully guaranteed if on the roster the 3rd day of the League Year.  In 2017 $6 million of his salary will become guaranteed if on the roster the 3rd day of the League Year.  If you want to see how the contract compares to others the NFL you can read my article on the contract.
Name: Cam Newton

Notes: Russell Wilson signed a four year contract extension with the Seahawks worth $87.6 million on July 31, 2015. According to SI\'s Peter King, Wilson received a $31 million signing bonus. Per Ian Rapoport of NFL.com the following tweet has the breakdown of the Wilson extension which we are using to estimate the cap charges at the moment. Wilson received $31.7 million fully guaranteed upon signing. His 2016, 2017, and $4.9 million of his 2018 salary are guaranteed for injury and will become fully guaranteed on the 5th day of the waiver period in each year. The total guarantee is $61.542 million.
Name: Russell Wilson

Notes: Ben Roethlisberger signed a 4 year contract extension with the Steelers on March 13, 2015. Details of the contract are based primarily on a report by Ed Bouchette of the Pittsburgh Post-Gazette. According to Bouchette, Roethlisberger received a $31 million signing bonus. The first three years of the contract are guaranteed for injury which is where the reported $65 million in guarantees comes from. $9 million in escalators are available in the final two contract years. The new contract saved the Steelers about $1.15 million in 2015 cap space.
Name: Ben Roethlisberger

Notes: Joe Flacco signed a three year contract extension with the Baltimore Ravens on March 2, 2016. The extension is worth $66.4 million in new money nd includes a $40 million signing bonus and $44 million fully guaranteed and $62 million in injury guarantees. The base salaries from the contract come from a report by the NFL\'s Albert Breer. Flacco had three years under contract when he signed the extension. He will earn an additional $26 million in compensation in 2016, $11.4 million in total new compensation over over two years, and $3.4 million over three years. The Ravens will reduce Flacco\'s 2016 cap number by $6 million and his 2017 cap number by $6.6 million
Name: Joe Flacco

Notes: Larry Pinkard signed a two year contract with the Jaguars on April 17, 2017. Please credit OTC if using this as your source.
Name: Larry Pinkard

Notes: Bobby Wagner signed a 4 year, $43 million contract extension on August 3, 2015.  According to Joel Corry, Wagner received an $8 million signing bonus and is due an option in 2016 worth $4 million. The cap charges being shown assume the option will be exercised. If the option is not exercised the cost to release Wagner in 2016 is $6.4 million. Wagner has $500,000 in per game roster bonuses in 2016 and $1 million in per game roster bonuses from 2017 through 2019. The guaranteed portion of the contract totals $21,977,427, with $8,977,427 being fully guaranteed. The remaining guarantees are for injury only but will vest during the waiver period of the specific seasons to full guarantees.
Name: Bobby Wagner

Notes: Ryan Kerrigan signed a five year contract extension worth $57.5 million with the Redskins on July 30, 2015. Kerrigan received a $16 million signing bonus. His 2015 and 2016 salaries are fully guaranteed to bring the full guarantee on the contract to $23.788 million. In each year o the contract Kerriga can earn up to $250,000 in roster bonuses for games active. The extension creates $800,000 in cap space for Washington in 2015.
Name: Ryan Kerrigan

Notes: Left tackle Nate Solder signed a two year extension worth $20.062 million with the New England Patriots on September 8, 2015. Contract information is based on a report by Jeff Howe of the Boston Herald. Solder received $19.938 million in fully guaranteed salary, including a $12.5 million signing bonus. Both his 2015 and 2016 salary are fully guaranteed. Solder can earn up to $500,000 in gameday roster bonuses and $500,000 in incentivized roster bonuses for making the Pro Bowl.  The extension reduces Solder\'s cap charge by $1.83 million.
Name: Nate Solder

Notes: Tyrod Taylor signed a five year, $90 million extension with the Buffalo Bills on August 13, 2016. Contract details come via a report by Mike Rodak of ESPN. Taylor\'s initial guarantee consists of $37 million of which $9.5 million is guaranteed upon signing and another $27.5 million is guaranteed for injury only. In 2017 the Bills can exercise a $15.5 million option on Taylor. If the Bills decline the option and fail to release Taylor, Taylor\'s 2017 salary wil escalate to a fully guaranteed $27.5 million. If the Bills pick up the option an additional $27.5 million in fully guaranteed salary can be earned in 2017 and 2018. Taylor can also earn additional incentives for performance. The dead money for the Bills if they release Taylor and decline the option is $2.85 million ad they will save $13.06 million in cap space. The numbers listed here represent a full option pickup. Prior to the start of the 2017 league year the Bills and Taylor agreed to a new two year contract in lieu of picking up Taylor\'s option. The new contract is worth $30.5 million with $15.5 million guaranteed at signing. The contract voids if Taylor is on the Bills roster 5 days after the start of the 2019 waiver period. If the two sides do not reach an agreement on an extension the prorated money from the 2020 and 2021 years will accelerate onto the Bills 2019 salary cap. The new contract saved the Bills $6.2 million in cap space in 2017.
Name: Tyrod Taylor

Name: Derek Anderson

Notes: Adrian Peterson signed a two year, $7 million contract with the Saints. According to Curtis Crabtree of PFT, Peterson received a $2.5 million signing bonus and will received a $750,000 roster bonus on the 3rd day of the 2018 league year. There are up to $1.65 million in per game roster bonuses in the contract. According to Nick Underhill of the Advocate, Peterson can earn up to $8.25 million in incentives. The incentives are up to $1 million for rushing yards, starting at $150,000 for 750 yards and maxing out at 1,500 yards. He can earn up to $750,000 in touchdown bonuses, beginning at $250,000 for 6 touchdowns and maxing out at 10 touchdowns. He can also earn up to $1 million for a Super Bowl win. Another $2.75 million is available as roster bonus escalators which are triggered based on earning the above incentives in 2017.
Name: Adrian Peterson

Notes: The Buffalo Bills agreed to trade for Lesean McCoy from the Philadelphia Eagles. The trade will not be official until March 10, 2015. McCoy will receive a $13.125 million signing bonus and a fully guarateed base salary in 2015 and $2.5 million guaranteed in 2016. In 2016 the balance of his salary for that year will be guaranteed if he is on the roster on the 1st day of the League Year. He also has a injury guarantee on his 2017 salary.
Name: LeSean McCoy

Notes: Matt Forte signed a three year, $12 million contract with the New York Jets on March 10, 2016. Forte received a $3 million signing bonus as part of his $9 million guarantee. Forte can earn $2 million in yearly escalators based on production.

Notes: CB Patrick Peterson signed a five year, $70.05 million contract extension with the Arizona Cardinals on July 30, 2014. Peterson had two years remaining on his contract at the time of signing. Petersons 2015 and 2016 base salaries are guaranteed for injury only and will vest as fully guaranteed salaries on the 5th day of the waiver period of each respective year. Peterson\'s 2017 base salary is also guaranteed for injury only and $5 million will become fully guaranteed if on the roster the 5th day of the 2016 waiver period with the remaining $4.75 million becoming fully guaranteed on the the 5th day of the 2017 waiver period. $630,866 of his 2018 salary  for injury only. If Peterson is on the Cardinals roster the 5th day of the 2017 waiver period he will earn an additional $4.75 million in full guarantees. The contract contains annual workout bonuses of $250,000 and a reporting bonus of $250,000 in 2020. Peterson converted $3.1 million of his salary into a signing bonus in 2016.

Notes: CB Richard Sherman signed a four year, $56 million contract extension with the Seattle Seahawks on May 7, 2014. The contract contains $40 million in guarantees of which $12.431 million is fully guaranteed. The fully guaranteed portion of the contract is made up of his 2014 base salary and an $11 million signing bonus. If Sherman is on the roster five days following the 2015 Super Bowl his $10 million 2015 base salary will become fully guaranteed. If he is on the roster five days after the 2016 Super Bowl his $12.569 million 2016 base salary and $5 million of his 2017 base salary will become fully guaranteed. Sherman\'s years salaries are $1,431,000(2014), $10,000,000(2015), $12,569,000(2016), $11,431,000(2017), and $11,000,000(2018).

Notes: Jimmy Graham signed a four year, $40 million contract with the New Orleans Saints on July 15, 2014. Graham\'s 2015 salary and $5 million roster bonus are both guaranteed for injury only and will become fully guaranteed on the 3rd day of the 2015 League Year. In 2017 Graham can earn a $2 million roster bonus if on the roster the 3rd day of the 2017 League Year. Graham was traded to the Seattle Seahawks on March 10, 2015. All terms from 2015 onward carry on to Seattle.
Name: Jimmy Graham

Notes: Avril signed a four year, $28.5 million contract with the Seahawks on December 19, 2014 . Avril received a $2.5 million signing bonus. Avril can earn up to $2.1 million in additional compensation based on sacks.
Name: Cliff Avril

Notes: LT Joe Staley signed a 6 year contract worth $44,650,000 with the San Francisco 49ers on July 18, 2014. The contract contains two option years in 2018 and 2019. Those option years must be exercised during the 2015 and 2016 League Year at a cost of $6 million and $4 million respectively. In each year of the contract Staley is eligible for $500,000 roster bonuses, which are paid out for each game in which he is active, as well as annual $200,000 workout bonuses. His option years also contain contract escalators based on performance. The base salaries of the contract are $2,700,000 (2014), $4,500,000(2015), $5,400,000(2016), $8,250,000(2017), $4,800,000(2017), and $4,800,000(2018). Staley had already been under contract with the 49ers through 2017, but this contract will be valued as an entirely new contract rather than an extension. Staley received no new money in 2014, but will receive an additional $12 million over the next three seasons of his original contract. In return for receiving larger up front money, Staley has given up free agency in 2018 and in return given the 49ers what would be considered reasonable salaries in 2018 and 2019 for a starting tackle.
Name: Joe Staley

Notes: Daniel Kilgore signed a three year, $5.25 million extension with the 49ers on February 27, 2014. Kilgore received a $1.35 million signing bonus and a fully guaranteed base salary in 2014. Name: Daniel Kilgore

Notes: Terron Armstead signed a five year, $65 million extension with the Saints on May 4, 2016. Armstead received $38 million in guarantees of which $20.88 million is fully guaranteed upon signing. The guarantee consists of an $11 million signing bonus, his 2016 and 2017 P5s, and  $5 million roster bonus due in 2017.  If Armstead is on the roster on the 2nd day of the 2017 League Year, $6.2 million of his 2018 salary becomes fully guaranteed with the balance vesting on the 3rd day of the 2018 legue year. If Armstead is on the roster on the 3rd day of the 2019 League Year another $6.92 million becomes fully guaranteed. From 2019 to 2021 Armstead can earn roster bonuses for being on the roster on the 3rd day of each respective season and also has annual $500,000 per game roster bonuses. According to ESPN\'s Field Yates, Armstead converted a $5 million roster bonus for 2017 into a signing bonus. The move creates $4 million in cap space for the Saints in 2017 but adds on $1 million in cap charges to each of the remaining years of the contract.
Name: Terron Armstead

Notes: Marshawn Lynch signed a new two year, $9 million contract with the Raiders following a trade with the Seahawks on April 26, 2017. $2.35 million is guaranteed, including a $1 million roster bonus and Lynch\'s 2017 salary. There is $500,000 in per game bonuses in 2017 and $750,000 in 2018. According to Mike Florio of PFT there is a large incentive package that Lynch can earn to increase the amount of the contract. The following breakdown comes from the PFT report: Lynch can earn up t0 $3.9 million in rushing incentives which starts at $400,000 for the first 400 yards and increases by another $400,000 for reaching 500 and 600 yards. At 800 yards the total increases to $600,000, which is also earned at 1,000 yards. For every 100 yards beyond 1,000, Lynch will earn $250,000 until the total bonus caps out at $3.9 million. If Lynch scores 9 touchdowns he will earn $250,000 and another $250,000 for 12 touchdowns. There are additional incentives in both 2017 and 2018 based on team performance.
Name: Marshawn Lynch

Notes: Morgan Moses signed a five year, $38.25 million contract extension with the Redskins on April 27, 2017. Per JI Halsell, Moses received $20 million in guarantees, $14.047 million of which is guaranteed at signing. $4.75 million will convert to fully guaranteed in 2019. We are estimating that Moses received a $9.5 million signing bonus and can earn up to $250,000 in per game bonuses in each year of the contract.  The new contract increases Moses\' 2017 cap number by $1.65 million. If using this information please cite OTC and Jimmy Halsell as the source of your data and link back to the appropriate pages to appropriately source your information.
Name: Morgan Moses

Notes: Derek Carr signed a five year, $125.025 million contract extension with the Raiders on June 22, 2017. The following breakdown of this contract comes from a report from Dan Graziano of ESPN so please cite him if using this information. Also please note that the backend salaries from 2020-2022 are estimated and likely are a bit lower in 2020 and 2021 and higher in 2022. I will update when I confirm the actual numbers but for right now they are estimates. Per Graziano, Carr received a $12.5 million signing bonus and a $7.5 million roster bonus in 2017. His 2017 base salary and a $15 million 2018 roster bonus are also guaranteed to bring the full guarantee on the contract to $40 million. Carr\'s 2018 and 2019 base salaries are guaranteed for injury at signing and will become fully guaranteed at the start of the waiver period of the 2018 and 2019 years. Carr has another $2.8 million guarantee in 2020 which brings the total guarantee to $70.2 million. Carr\'s 2017 cap number increased by $14,022,481.
Name: Derek Carr
